{
  "stem": "3022.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "After we moved in, we were treated the way some black families are treated when they move-- when they're the first families that move in the white neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I spent two weeks in bed recovering from the beating that I received from-- from the children in the neighborhood and who later became my friends, with whom I later played soccer, and who were the ones who stood guard at the entrance of the street so that the mob would not come and plunder.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But the-- the-- as I was growing up, the anti-Semitic trend in Poland became more and more apparent to me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "In 1935, when Marshal Pilsudski passed away-- Marshal Pilsudski was the marshal, wasn't the dictator, but he was the head of the Polish government.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And he tried to make sure that the Jews were afforded some protection.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But with his-- with his passing, many of the laws that they tried to institute became-- you know, were put on books.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "One of the laws was the law of ritual slaughter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They tried to abolish ritual slaughter altogether.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "But they finally compromised, and they allowed about one third of the amount of animals that were slaughtered for kosher meat to be slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And things became very tough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "My father lost his job, and the butcher shop that he opened afterwards wouldn't function.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "There were many economic hardships that were-- that were upon the Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "For instance, just to give an example, we had only one savings and loan association in Poland called the PKO, which was Pocztowa Kasa Oszczednosci, which is the Polish savings and loan association.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "It was affiliated with the post office.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "They had over 10,000 offices through Poland. 60% of the money that was deposited in there was Jewish deposits.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
